    {
      "id": "description",
      "title": "Description",
      "body": "Starrberget is a south facing vertical to off-vertical crag that dries out quickly. All routes are bolted."
    },
    {
      "id": "directions",
      "title": "Directions",
      "body": "From Umeå, drive E12 towards Vännäs. At the crossroad after Vännesby take right on E12 towards Mo I Rana and continue 2 km and park at a pull-out on the right side. Follow a track up to a small cliff with some bolts on your right, walk straight past this and take a small path on your right. There will be a birch with a carving of a K in it. Kategori:sport Kategori:vertikalt Kategori:sva Kategori:Västerbotten Kategori:Engelska"
    }
